TRAVEL POLICY

Purpose
This policy governs official business travel and reimbursement procedures.

Travel Authorization
Employees must obtain approval from their manager before booking business travel.

Air Travel
Economy class airfare is reimbursable for domestic and international travel.
Business class travel requires senior management approval.

Accommodation
Employees may stay in company-approved hotels during business trips.
Hotel expenses up to USD 150 per night are reimbursable.

Meals
Meal expenses up to USD 50 per day are reimbursable upon submission of receipts.

Local Transportation
Taxi, rideshare, airport shuttle, and public transportation expenses related to business travel are reimbursable.

Expense Claims
Employees must submit travel expense reports within 15 days of completing the trip.

Reimbursement Timeline
Approved travel expenses are reimbursed within 10 business days after claim approval.

Non-Reimbursable Expenses
Personal entertainment, fines, and non-business-related expenses will not be reimbursed.
